Platform support for squashfs tools
===================================

Common issues
-------------
GMAKE: Build with `gmake', installing it if necessary
GCC: Build with CC=gcc, installing it if necessary
NOXATTR: Build with XATTR_SUPPORT=0, no Linux-compatible extended attribute
	support available.
NOCPU: Can't auto-detect the number of CPUs available.

Platforms
---------
Linux: Everything works
Mac OS X: Everything works
FreeBSD: GMAKE, NOXATTR
NetBSD: GMAKE
OpenBSD: GMAKE, NOXATTR
DragonflyBSD: GMAKE, NOXATTR
OpenIndiana: GCC, NOXATTR, install `header-math' package
Solaris: GMAKE, GCC, NOXATTR
QNX: GCC, NOXATTR, NOCPU
Hurd: NOXATTR, NOCPU
Haiku: NOXATTR, NOCPU
Windows/cygwin: Install make and gcc

Android: NOXATTR
	- Cross-compile using appropriate flags

Minix: CC, NOXATTR, NOCPU
	- No preemptive threads, build against pthread by settin
		CPPFLAGS=-I/usr/pkg/include LDFLAGS=-L/usr/pkg/lib
